# Wazuh SIEM Server -----------------------------------------------------------
## Wazuh Manager Configuration (CRITICAL - controls all agent behavior)
### Changes here affect the entire fleet of monitored hosts
-a always,exit -F arch=b64 -S openat2,openat,open,unlink,unlinkat,rename,renameat,renameat2 -F dir=/var/ossec/etc/ -F perm=wa -k wazuh_config
-a always,exit -F arch=b64 -S openat2,openat,open -F path=/var/ossec/etc/ossec.conf -F perm=wa -k wazuh_config

## Wazuh Rulesets and Decoders
### Custom rules and decoders — an attacker could blind the SIEM by modifying these
-a always,exit -F arch=b64 -S openat2,openat,open,unlink,unlinkat,rename,renameat,renameat2 -F dir=/var/ossec/etc/rules/ -F perm=wa -k wazuh_rules
-a always,exit -F arch=b64 -S openat2,openat,open,unlink,unlinkat,rename,renameat,renameat2 -F dir=/var/ossec/etc/decoders/ -F perm=wa -k wazuh_rules
-a always,exit -F arch=b64 -S openat2,openat,open,unlink,unlinkat,rename,renameat,renameat2 -F dir=/var/ossec/ruleset/ -F perm=wa -k wazuh_rules

## Wazuh Shared Agent Configuration
### Group-level configurations pushed to agents — tampering affects entire groups
-a always,exit -F arch=b64 -S openat2,openat,open,unlink,unlinkat,rename,renameat,renameat2 -F dir=/var/ossec/etc/shared/ -F perm=wa -k wazuh_shared_config

## Wazuh Active Response Scripts
### These scripts are executed automatically in response to alerts
### An attacker replacing these could achieve remote code execution across the fleet
-a always,exit -F arch=b64 -S openat2,openat,open,unlink,unlinkat,rename,renameat,renameat2 -F dir=/var/ossec/active-response/bin/ -F perm=wa -k wazuh_active_response

## Wazuh Integration Scripts
### Integrations with Slack, PagerDuty, VirusTotal, etc.
-a always,exit -F arch=b64 -S openat2,openat,open,unlink,unlinkat,rename,renameat,renameat2 -F dir=/var/ossec/integrations/ -F perm=wa -k wazuh_integrations

## Wazuh Binaries and Libraries
### Replacement of Wazuh binaries is a high-severity supply chain attack
-a always,exit -F arch=b64 -S openat2,openat,open,unlink,unlinkat,rename,renameat,renameat2 -F dir=/var/ossec/bin/ -F perm=wa -k wazuh_binaries
-a always,exit -F arch=b64 -S openat2,openat,open,unlink,unlinkat,rename,renameat,renameat2 -F dir=/var/ossec/lib/ -F perm=wa -k wazuh_binaries

## Wazuh Agent Key Management (CRITICAL)
### The client.keys file contains authentication keys for ALL agents
### Compromise of this file allows impersonation of any monitored host
-a always,exit -F arch=b64 -S openat2,openat,open -F path=/var/ossec/etc/client.keys -F perm=wa -k wazuh_agent_keys
-a always,exit -F arch=b64 -S openat2,openat,open -F path=/var/ossec/etc/client.keys -F perm=r -F auid>=1000 -F auid!=-1 -k wazuh_agent_keys_read

